@@yThe Cathedral of the Violet Eclipse@@N

@@eThe Cathedral sits along the western approaches from Midgaard toward the Roc
Road, close enough for supply from the city's stonewrights yet far enough
outside Watch circuits that hazardous reliquary work could proceed without
civic alarm. Built to be reachable but deniable.@@N

@@dIt began as the Violet Arch Chapel-House, a sanctioned reliquary checkpoint
of the Violet Compact era. Its charter duties were threshold adjudication for
relic-bearing caravans, ritual quarantine for unclassified artifacts, and
archive relay where oaths and confessions were copied in Lantern Registry
shorthand. Violet pigments and amethyst lanterns were not occult markers but
administrative ones, indicating Compact jurisdiction.@@N

@@yAs decades passed, the chapel-house accumulated influence through the same
institutional corruption that had already repurposed Midgaard's registry to
process condemned persons as 'arcane material.' Families sought private
rulings in its side chapels. Guild officers paid for accelerated attestation.
Convoy commanders learned that a favorable seal could erase delays and
contradictions before cargo reached Midgaard's inner inspectors.@@N

@@rThe decisive rupture came during the Silenced Vespers. Reform clerks
attempted to publish contradictory ledgers proving that high-born petitioners
received absolution while bonded laborers were condemned under identical
evidence. Before those records reached public dockets, bell-lines went
silent. Outer doors were sealed. The surviving clergy declared the
institution 'withdrawn into eclipse until judgment ripens.'@@N

@@eNo Midgaard magistrate challenged the withdrawal. The chapel-house became
a closed system. From that withdrawal emerged the Cathedral, where beauty
became a filing system for grief and civic metadata was declared divine.@@N

@@dIts Fivefold Occlusion litany encodes the corruption: color reveals rank,
rank determines witness, witness determines memory, memory determines
sentence, sentence determines who may be named. Where Midgaard's civic
tradition held truth as plural and auditable, the Eclipse doctrine teaches
that truth requires institutional mediation to become legally real.@@N
